Source: rpc2
Section: libdevel
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Jan Harkes <jaharkes@cs.cmu.edu>
Standards-Version: 3.8.4
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 7), liblwp-dev, flex, bison | byacc, libreadline-dev, pkg-config, liblua5.1-dev

Package: librpc2-dev
Architecture: amd64 arm i386 m68k powerpc sparc
Provides: rpc2-tools
Replaces: rpc2-tools
Depends: librpc2-5 (= ${binary:Version}), ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Remote procedure call library, development files
 RPC2 is a remote procedure call library developed at CMU. It is layered
 on top of UDP sockets and is used by the Coda distributed filesystem
 .
 This package contains the required libraries and headers and support
 programs to develop applications that use RPC2.

Package: librpc2-5-dbg
Section: debug
Architecture: amd64 arm i386 m68k powerpc sparc
Priority: extra
Depends: librpc2-5 (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: Remote procedure call library debug symbol
 Debug symbols for the 'RPC2' remote procedure call library.

Package: librpc2-5
Section: libs
Architecture: amd64 arm i386 m68k powerpc sparc
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Conflicts: librpc2-4
Homepage: http://www.coda.cs.cmu.edu
Description: Remote procedure call library
 RPC2 is a remote procedure call library developed at CMU. It is layered
 on top of UDP sockets and is used by the Coda distributed filesystem
 .
 This package contains the run-time libraries needed for applications that
 use RPC2.

